<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Fundamentals - Learn Frontend</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header class="header">
        <h1>üé® CSS Fundamentals</h1>
        <p>Master layouts with Flexbox and Grid</p>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <section class="card">
            <h2>The Box Model</h2>
            <div class="box-model-demo">
                <div class="box">Content</div>
            </div>
            <p>Every element is a box with: content, padding, border, and margin.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Flexbox Layout</h2>
            <div class="flex-demo">
                <div class="flex-item">1</div>
                <div class="flex-item">2</div>
                <div class="flex-item">3</div>
            </div>
            <p>Flexbox is perfect for one-dimensional layouts (rows or columns).</p>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Grid Layout</h2>
            <div class="grid-demo">
                <div class="grid-item">1</div>
                <div class="grid-item">2</div>
                <div class="grid-item">3</div>
                <div class="grid-item">4</div>
                <div class="grid-item">5</div>
                <div class="grid-item">6</div>
            </div>
            <p>Grid is ideal for two-dimensional layouts.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="card highlight">
            <h2>‚úèÔ∏è Exercise</h2>
            <p><strong>Tasks:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Create a responsive navbar using Flexbox</li>
                <li>Build a card grid that adapts to screen size</li>
                <li>Add hover effects to buttons</li>
                <li>Create a responsive footer with 3 columns</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Responsive Design</h2>
            <p>Resize your browser window to see responsive changes!</p>
            <div class="responsive-demo">
                <div class="responsive-box">Box 1</div>
                <div class="responsive-box">Box 2</div>
                <div class="responsive-box">Box 3</div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
        <p>Practice makes perfect! Keep styling üé®</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
